	<h1>XML and Javascript Information</h1>
	<h3>What is XML?</h3>
	<p>XML, which stands for eXtensive Markup Language, is a language that was created to carry and store information. Unlike HTML, it will not display information. Separate programming must still be used.</p>
	<br>
	<h3>How is XML used?</h3>
	<p>XML is used with tags that are made up by the document author, as opposed to HTML which has its own set of predefined tags. Adding, removing, or modifying data is simple in XML, too.</p>
	<br>
	<h3>XML Example:</h3>
	<p>XML would look something like this.
		<\message>
			<\to> Professor <\/to>
			<\from> Cory <\/from>
			<\body> Here is my XML assignment! <\/body>
		<\/message>
	</p>